  "description": "Fix Gallery Card Body Display Issue on Gallery List Page\n\nResolve the issue where gallery card bodies are not rendering on the gallery list page, resulting in blank spaces where content should appear.\n\nRequirements:\n- Locate the gallery list page component and identify the gallery-card-body elements\n- Investigate why the card body content is not visible (CSS display issue, missing data, rendering condition, z-index problem)\n- Verify that data is being fetched and passed correctly to the card components\n- Check for CSS issues that might be hiding content (opacity: 0, visibility: hidden, display: none, color matching background)\n- Ensure proper HTML structure and class names are applied\n- Verify no JavaScript errors are preventing render\n- Test that card body content displays correctly for all galleries in the list\n- Confirm layout and spacing appear as intended once visible\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Empty or missing gallery data\n- Long text content that might overflow\n- Different gallery types or categories\n- Responsive behavior on various screen sizes",
